        <section><title>split pane (ROLE_SPLIT_PANE)</title>
          <para>A split pane is a specialized panel that presents two panels
            at once.  It has a divider than can be dragged.</para>
          <section><title>Braille</title>
            <para>The words "split pane" will become part of the context and
              the focused object will be the object of interest.  In the
              event the focus is on the split pane divider, braille will
              display the percentage of the top or left pane that is shown
              followed by "split pane divider".</para>
            <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>Verbose Example: open file dialog directory split pane /usr list 5 of 10</para>
              </listitem>
              <listitem>
                <para>Brief Example: open file dialog directory split pane /usr list 5 of 10</para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
          </section>

